<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-22T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-22T03:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512 Likin/44: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-22T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 22,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 22—9:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>786. Legation’s 783, October 17, 8 p.m. Following from Swatow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“October 19, 1 p.m. My telegram of October 6, noon. Local
                                    government likin authorities are now recognizing inward transit
                                    certificates. No further action should be taken. Forwarding full
                                    report by mail.”<note n="76" xml:id="d506fn76">Not
                                        printed.</note></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>